  "cumulative_summary": "## Research Progress Summary (Plans v1→v4)\n\n### Active Baseline\n- **active-signal-v1-regime-gate@2**: Sharpe 1.385, PnL $1520.78, 388 trades, max DD 3.08%, WR 50.26%, PF 1.494\n\n### Promoted Features (in regime-gate@2)\n- Regime gate filter (active since v1)\n\n### Rejected Approaches with Evidence\n1. **cf_funding_regime** (v3): Sharpe 1.105, PnL $1149.62, 326 trades — Raw funding_rate not available in event data; only settlement timing columns exist. Massive PnL/trade degradation.\n2. **cf_momentum_divergence** (v3): Sharpe 1.385, PnL $1501.80, 380 trades — Feature already existed/published. Marginal PnL loss (-$19), fewer trades (-8), no DD improvement. Net negative.\n3. Previous volatility filters and entry-suppression layers (v1-v2): All degraded trade count without sufficient PnL improvement to compensate.\n\n### Key Insight\nEntry-suppression/filter approaches are **exhausted** — the regime gate already provides optimal filtering. Further suppression always reduces trades and PnL proportionally. New approaches must generate **new signal information** (ML predictions) or exploit **orthogonal data dimensions** (settlement timing, trend exhaustion states).\n\n### Anti-Patterns\n- DO NOT pursue more entry filters or signal suppression layers\n- DO NOT assume funding event data contains raw funding_rate — only settlement timing is available\n- DO NOT re-test cf_momentum_divergence — already published and tested\n- DO NOT clone strategies without validating after adding features",
